table multiprocessing_extra113.mp_syncmanager_identity:
  description: "multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager class identity checks in mpbm113 namespace — wave 255 theme: multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__name__.__eq__('SyncManager')==True (len=11: 'SyncManager'=11; SyncManager is a concrete implementation of BaseManager that provides managed versions of common synchronization primitives: Lock, RLock, Semaphore, BoundedSemaphore, Event, Condition, Queue, Namespace, etc.); multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__name__.__len__()==11; multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__qualname__.__eq__('SyncManager')==True (len=11; qualname equals name for top-level class); multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.managers')==True (len=24: 'multiprocessing.managers'=24; same module as BaseManager); multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__module__.__len__()==24; multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__mro__.__len__()==3 (MRO=[SyncManager, BaseManager, object]; 3-level chain — one deeper than BaseManager whose MRO has len=2); multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('BaseManager')==True (SyncManager inherits directly from BaseManager); compare: BaseManager.__mro__.__len__()==2 ([BaseManager, object]) < SyncManager.__mro__.__len__()==3 (adds BaseManager as intermediate); compare class name lengths: SyncManager.__name__.__len__()==11 == BaseManager.__name__.__len__()==11 (coincidental tie: both 11 chars); multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__name__.__len__()==11 ties with BaseManager.__name__.__len__()==11; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: mpbm113b

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
