invariant multiprocessing_extra113.BaseManager_three_way_tie_at_20:
  description: "multiprocessing.managers.BaseManager.register.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 20 — 'BaseManager.register' = 'BaseManager.'=12 + 'register'=8 = 20; this is part of the three-way tie at len=20 in this spec: register==__init__==__exit__==20 (all have 8-char method names: 'register'=8, '__init__'=8, '__exit__'=8); multiprocessing.managers.BaseManager.register.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseManager.register')==True; multiprocessing.managers.BaseManager.__init__.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==20 (same value); multiprocessing.managers.BaseManager.__exit__.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==20 (same value); note: the tie is caused by the coincidence that 'register', '__init__', and '__exit__' all have exactly 8 characters; compare: __enter__ (9 chars, len=21) is the longest; start (5 chars, len=17) is the shortest; the three-way tie at 20 is a distinctive feature of the BaseManager co_qualname set in this spec; first standalone invariant documenting the three-way tie; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: multiprocessing.managers.BaseManager.register.__code__.co_qualname.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 20

